@martinwicke - regarding your comment on `create_example_parser_from_signatures`, I tried to backtrace it's usage and found that the only usage of this function is in `estimator.py` at 

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/12864026/23106148/e57fea4a-f6e0-11e6-8ee6-3d3e82734c58.png)

which is **deprecated**. Further, this deprecated function is used in `export.py` at one place 

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/12864026/23106161/28b61492-f6e1-11e6-89a8-0cb0cff3afa8.png)

which is **deprecated** as well. As such, I am not sure what is the reason to fix this? 

Anyways, I have made some changes that might fix the problem, but since there are no tests that fail, I have no way of testing.

Please let me know what you think.
